JOUBERTON cops in the North West have launched a manhunt after eight suspects entered a tavern in Extension 23, on Saturday, 23 July, and allegedly robbed patrons. According to Colonel Adele Myburgh, it’s alleged that the suspects threatened patrons and fired a few shots before robbing some of them of their cellphones. “A 42-year-old tavern owner was instructed to open the cash register and upon refusing, he was shot in the stomach and admitted to a local hospital, where he’s in a stable condition. No other injuries were reported,” Myburgh said in a statement. ALSO READ: TAVERN SHOOTING: EMPD officer arrested! She said the robbers reportedly broke a burglar door leading into the owner’s house. “They took an undisclosed amount of cash and fled to a nearby field where they got into two vehicles, a white Toyota Quantum and a white bakkie,” Myburgh said. She urged anyone with information that could assist the police to contact Warrant Officer Mangaliso Mosiea on 072 476 4679, or call CrimeStop on 08600 10111. Alternatively, anonymous tip-offs can be logged on the MySAPS App.